The paper proposes a deep learning algorithm for estimating the ensemble average propagator (EAP) from diffusion magnetic resonance imaging (dMRI) data. This involves using a basis and associated coefficients to describe the diffusion profile, and the authors choose the SHORE basis. The paper focuses on the design of a deep network to estimate the coefficients, and includes an auxiliary output for approximated fiber orientation (FO) errors to regularize the training. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and information theory (cs.IT).
